div.p:
2:7. He that hath an ear.—To receive and understand
the voice of God through His Word.—Matthew 11:15;
13:9, 43; Rev. 13:9.

Having seven horns.—Perfect power. All power is
given unto Me in Heaven and in earth.—Matt. 28:18;
1 Sam. 2:1, 10; Deut. 33:17; 1 Ki. 22:11.

And seven eyes.—Perfect wisdom. In whom are hid
all the treasures of wisdom and knowledge.—Col. 2:3;
Zech. 3:9; 4:10; Rev. 1:4; 3:1; 4:5; 2 Chron. 16:9.

And for the testimony.—And through the testimony;
through the Word of God. The word dia is here used
again. It is the Word that does the beheading.

Clothed with white robes.—They let slip their opportunity
for becoming members of the Bride; but they are,
nevertheless, virgins, pure in their heart-intentions.—F. 127;
Rev. 7:14.

Shall feed them.—Be their shepherd. (John 10:1-28;
21:16.) They will not have immortality. Their lives will
always require to be sustained, as in the case of the angels.

And as it were a great mountain.—England in the time
of Henry VIII. Mountains symbolize kingdoms.—Dan. 2:35;
Jer. 51:25.

Of the ships.—Independent bodies of Christian worshippers
called Lollards, followers of Wycliffe.—Mark 4:36;
6:48-51; John 6:21.

Who created Heaven, and the things that therein are.—The
heavens declare the glory of God.—Psa. 19:1-6;
Neh. 9:6; Rev. 4:11; 14:7.

Give me the little book.—Take me into Your confidence;
give me Your Holy Spirit; show me, as promised, the
things to come.—John 16:13.

Of [His] THE testament of God.—The Secret—The
Finished Mystery.—Psa. 25:14; Col. 1:27; Rev. 14:17;
16:1, 17.

A Woman.—The early Church, Nominal Zion, (D. 591),
originally a chaste Virgin.—2 Cor. 11:2; Matt. 9:15; 22:2;
John 3:29; Eph. 5:25, 32.

13:5. And there was given unto him a mouth.—The
mouth of Antichrist is one of its leading characteristics.—B. 305;
Dan. 7:8, 11, 25.

13:8. And all that dwell upon the earth shall worship
him.—Yield either willing or forced obedience to his mandates;
bow the knee in submission.

Into the cup of His indignation.—The Lord our God
hath put us to silence and given us water of gall to drink,
because we have sinned against the Lord.—Jer. 8:14;
Isa. 51:17-20; Jer. 25:26-28; Rev. 18:6; 16:19; Psa. 60:3;
75:8.

Having on His head a golden crown.—The Divine nature,
Immortality, the highest form of life.—2 Tim. 4:8;
Jas. 1:12; 1 Pet. 5:4.

And gather the clusters of the vine of the earth.—In
the Adventist cluster there are 6 bunches of smaller sects;
in the Baptist 15; Brethren (Dunkard) 4; Plymouth
Brethren 4; River Brethren 3; Catholic Apostolic 2;
Churches of the Living God 3; Churches of the New Jerusalem
2; Disciples of Christ 2; Evangelical Bodies 2;
Faith Associations 9; Friends 4; Latter-Day Saints 2;
Lutheran 21; Scandinavian Evangelical Bodies 3; Mennonite
13; Methodist 16; Moravian 2; Pentecostal bodies
2; Presbyterian 12; Protestant Episcopal 2; Reformed 4;
United Brethren 2.

Having seven heads and ten horns.—See Rev. 12:3; 13:1:
17:9-12; Dan. 7:7, 20; Rev. 5:6; 1 Sam. 2:10; Deut. 33:17;
1 Ki. 22:11.

17:14. These shall make war with the Lamb.—Endeavor
to suppress the message of Present Truth.—Rev. 16:14;
19:19.

Fell down and worshipped God that sat on the Throne, saying Amen;
Alleluia.—The God, the mighty One, here
referred to is the Lord Jesus.—Rev. 5:3.

I am thy fellowservant.—St. John in his humility forgets
his own share in imparting the revelation; and the
Angel in his humility brings this to light (Acts 10:25, 26).—Cook;
Acts 14:14, 15; Rev. 22:9; Rom. 1:1; Phil. 1:1;
Tit. 1:1; 2 Pet. 1:1.

21:10. And he carried me away in the Spirit.—God
hath revealed them unto us by His Spirit.—1 Cor. 2:10;
Rev. 1:10; 17:3.

22:15. [For] without are dogs.—There will be no clergy
class, as such, in the Kingdom.—Isa. 56:10; Phil. 3:2;
2 Tim. 3:8, 9.

Putteth forth—Behold the fig tree, and all the trees;
when they now shoot forth ... know ye that the
Kingdom of God is nigh.

From the lions' dens—You are now in the lions' dens,
but look beyond them. Satan goes about as a roaring lion;
but no lion shall be there.

7:2. Thy navel—Umbilical cord; by which you are
joined to the Oath-bound Covenant, the Sarah Covenant;
the cord of faith.

To clusters of grapes—Suggestive of food and refreshment
for the hungry, when they shall suck and be satisfied,
milk out and be delighted.

quote.p:
Five—Used in connection with ten, completeness in
the stage, degree, or power attained or ordained;
a symbol of Divinity.
